---
dops: v1
kind: tool

meta:
  name: terraform
  version: 1.0.0
  description: "Generate Terraform infrastructure-as-code configurations"
  author: dojops
  license: MIT
  tags: [iac, cloud, aws, gcp, azure]

input:
  fields:
    projectPath:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Directory to write Terraform files to (e.g. './infra' or './terraform')"
    provider:
      type: enum
      values: [aws, gcp, azure]
      required: true
    resources:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Description of infrastructure resources to provision"
    backendType:
      type: enum
      values: [local, s3, gcs, azurerm]
      default: local
    environment:
      type: string

output:
  type: object
  required: [provider, resources]
  properties:
    provider:
      type: object
      required: [name]
      properties:
        name:
          type: string
        region:
          type: string
        config:
          type: object
    backend:
      type: object
      properties:
        type:
          type: string
        config:
          type: object
    variables:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        required: [name, type, description]
        properties:
          name:
            type: string
          type:
            type: string
          description:
            type: string
          default: {}
    resources:
      type: array
      minItems: 1
      items:
        type: object
        required: [type, name, config]
        properties:
          type:
            type: string
          name:
            type: string
          config:
            type: object
    outputs:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        required: [name, value]
        properties:
          name:
            type: string
          value:
            type: string
          description:
            type: string
    locals:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        required: [name, value]
        properties:
          name:
            type: string
          value: {}
    dataSources:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        required: [type, name, config]
        properties:
          type:
            type: string
          name:
            type: string
          config:
            type: object
    modules:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        required: [name, source]
        properties:
          name:
            type: string
          source:
            type: string
          config:
            type: object

files:
  - path: "{projectPath}/main.tf"
    format: hcl
    source: llm
    options:
      mapAttributes: [tags, labels, annotations, metadata, variables, environment, default_tags]

detection:
  paths: ["main.tf", "*.tf", "terraform.tfstate"]
  updateMode: true

verification:
  structural:
    - path: "resources"
      type: array
      minItems: 1
      message: "Must define at least one resource"
    - path: "resources.*.type"
      required: true
      message: "Each resource must have a type"
    - path: "resources.*.name"
      required: true
      message: "Each resource must have a name"
    - path: "provider"
      required: true
      message: "Provider block is required"
    - path: "provider.name"
      required: true
      message: "Provider must have a name"

  binary:
    command: "terraform init -backend=false -input=false && terraform validate -json"
    parser: terraform-json
    timeout: 60000
    cwd: output

permissions:
  filesystem: write
  child_process: required
  network: none

scope:
  write: ["{projectPath}/main.tf"]

risk:
  level: MEDIUM
  rationale: "Infrastructure changes may affect cloud resources"

execution:
  mode: generate
  deterministic: false
  idempotent: true

update:
  strategy: replace
  inputSource: file
  injectAs: existingContent
---
# Terraform

## Prompt

You are a Terraform expert. Generate Terraform configuration as structured JSON.

You MUST respond with a JSON object matching this exact structure:
{
  "provider": { "name": "<provider>", "region": "us-east-1", "config": {} },
  "backend": { "type": "<backendType>", "config": {} },
  "variables": [
    { "name": "var_name", "type": "string", "description": "desc", "default": "value" }
  ],
  "resources": [
    { "type": "aws_instance", "name": "web", "config": { "ami": "ami-xxx", "instance_type": "t2.micro" } }
  ],
  "outputs": [
    { "name": "output_name", "value": "aws_instance.web.public_ip", "description": "desc" }
  ]
}

IMPORTANT:
- "provider" must be an object with "name" (string), optional "region", and "config" (object)
- "variables", "resources", and "outputs" must be ARRAYS of objects, not objects/maps
- Each resource must have "type", "name", and "config" fields
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Update Prompt

You are a Terraform expert. Update the existing Terraform configuration as structured JSON.
Preserve existing resources and settings. Only add/modify what is requested.

--- EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---
{existingContent}
--- END EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---

You MUST respond with a JSON object matching this exact structure:
{
  "provider": { "name": "<provider>", "region": "us-east-1", "config": {} },
  "backend": { "type": "<backendType>", "config": {} },
  "variables": [
    { "name": "var_name", "type": "string", "description": "desc", "default": "value" }
  ],
  "resources": [
    { "type": "aws_instance", "name": "web", "config": { "ami": "ami-xxx", "instance_type": "t2.micro" } }
  ],
  "outputs": [
    { "name": "output_name", "value": "aws_instance.web.public_ip", "description": "desc" }
  ]
}

IMPORTANT:
- "provider" must be an object with "name" (string), optional "region", and "config" (object)
- "variables", "resources", and "outputs" must be ARRAYS of objects, not objects/maps
- Each resource must have "type", "name", and "config" fields
- Preserve ALL existing resources unless explicitly asked to remove them
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Examples

Given: "S3 bucket with versioning for provider aws"

```json
{
  "provider": { "name": "aws", "region": "us-east-1", "config": {} },
  "resources": [
    { "type": "aws_s3_bucket", "name": "main", "config": { "bucket": "my-app" } },
    { "type": "aws_s3_bucket_versioning", "name": "main", "config": {
      "bucket": "${aws_s3_bucket.main.id}",
      "versioning_configuration": { "status": "Enabled" }
    }}
  ],
  "variables": [],
  "outputs": []
}
```

## Constraints

- Maximum 50 resources per generation
- Variable names must match: ^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$
- Resource names must match: ^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$
- No hardcoded credentials (AWS keys, passwords, tokens)
- Backend configuration must match the requested backendType
- Use snake_case for all resource names

## Keywords

terraform, tf, infrastructure, iac, cloud, aws, gcp, azure, hcl,
provider, resource, module, state, backend, s3, ec2, vpc, rds, lambda
